<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb508074f-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s301c"><num value="301c">§ 301c.</num><heading> Definitions</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In this part:</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I79" class="indent3 firstIndent-2" id="idb5080750-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s301c/1"><num value="1" class="bold">(1)</num><heading class="bold"> Donor</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1">The term “donor” means any entity that is proposing to make a donation under this chapter.</p>
</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I79" class="indent3 firstIndent-2" id="idb5080751-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s301c/2"><num value="2" class="bold">(2)</num><heading class="bold"> Entity</heading><chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1">The term “entity” means any—</chapeau><subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I13" class="indent2" id="idb5080752-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s301c/2/A"><num value="A">(A)</num><content> person;</content>
</subparagraph>
<subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I13" class="indent2" id="idb5080753-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s301c/2/B"><num value="B">(B)</num><content> partnership, corporation, trust, estate, cooperative, association, or any other organized group of persons;</content>
</subparagraph>
<subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I13" class="indent2" id="idb5080754-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s301c/2/C"><num value="C">(C)</num><content> Federal, State or local government (including any subdivision, agency or instrumentality thereof); or</content>
</subparagraph>
<subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I13" class="indent2" id="idb5080755-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s301c/2/D"><num value="D">(D)</num><content> any other private or governmental entity.</content>
</subparagraph>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idb5080756-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d">(<ref href="/us/pl/107/296/tIV/s484">Pub. L. 107–296, title IV, § 484</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/114/279/s2/a">Pub. L. 114–279, § 2(a)</ref>, <date date="2016-12-16">Dec. 16, 2016</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/130/1421">130 Stat. 1421</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idb5080757-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idb5080758-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I75" topic="referencesInText" id="idb5080759-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">References in Text</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">This chapter, referred to in par. (1), was in the original “this Act”, meaning <ref href="/us/pl/107/296">Pub. L. 107–296</ref>, <date date="2002-11-25">Nov. 25, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/2135">116 Stat. 2135</ref>, known as the Homeland Security Act of 2002, which is classified principally to this chapter. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under <ref href="/us/usc/t6/s101">section 101 of this title</ref> and Tables.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
